{"key":"post-11121844","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11121844</id>\n<content>You don't use fans on flowhoods, you use blowers.&amp;nbsp; A fan will cavitate rather than blow through something like a flow hood.&amp;nbsp; A blower for the smallest 12&quot; X 24&quot; flowhood filter will need to be at least 1/5 HP and have a squirrel cage blower attached.&amp;nbsp; Make sure it's rated at the flow you require at +/- 1&quot; W.G.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11121933</next>\n<prev>11121810</prev>\n<first>11120934</first>\n<last>11122200</last>\n<when>1253847761</when>\n<utime>09/25/09 06:02 AM</utime>\n</post>"}